cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with incorporating syntactic information in Neural Machine Translation models. It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new method for learning a neural attentional transduction model. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it deals with neural machine translation models. Finally, it could also be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as it deals with learning from parse trees, which is a common technique in computer vision.
